WEBVTT

00:11.900 --> 00:13.300
[TV static drones]

00:13.367 --> 00:16.266
[bright tone]

00:16.333 --> 00:19.266
[tense, jazzy music]

00:19.333 --> 00:26.367
♪ ♪

01:47.533 --> 01:52.166
- "The best laid schemes of mice
and men most often go astray."

01:52.233 --> 01:53.600
That was written by
Mr. Robert Burns

01:53.667 --> 01:58.667
way the fuck back in 1785,
and it still is news.

01:58.734 --> 02:01.333
In Oz, we got
all sorts of schemes

02:01.400 --> 02:03.266
to change our
lousy, lonely lives,

02:03.333 --> 02:06.233
but no matter how much
we plot and plan,

02:06.300 --> 02:08.266
something outside
our control

02:08.333 --> 02:11.533
always comes along
and fucks things up.

02:13.600 --> 02:15.667
You take Tobias Beecher--

02:15.734 --> 02:17.200
six months ago,
if you'd have asked him

02:17.266 --> 02:18.734
where he planned to be today,

02:18.800 --> 02:21.433
he'd have said at his daughter's
fourth birthday party.

02:21.500 --> 02:22.867
Instead he's howling
at the moon,

02:22.934 --> 02:27.000
thanks to some bad angel dust.
- [screaming]

02:27.066 --> 02:29.500
- Old Vern Schillinger--
before he got to Oz,

02:29.567 --> 02:31.667
he wanted to get America
back on the right track,

02:31.734 --> 02:33.567
the white track.

02:33.633 --> 02:37.533
Now Beecher smashed a piece of
glass in his pure Aryan eye.

02:37.600 --> 02:40.133
[intense, percussive music]

02:40.200 --> 02:42.867
Timmy McManus--
he's slowly watching

02:42.934 --> 02:45.834
as his dreams for the perfect
prison fart away.

02:47.033 --> 02:49.700
And then there's
the Reverend Kareem Said.

02:49.767 --> 02:52.333
He was working on a way
to bring the brothers together,

02:52.400 --> 02:55.500
to fight the injustices we
endure in the name of justice.

02:55.567 --> 02:57.934
He was working it
and working it,

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
till a heart attack
worked him over.

03:00.066 --> 03:01.967
- Huseni Mershah,

03:02.033 --> 03:04.100
this is Kareem Said.

03:04.166 --> 03:07.600
- Maybe Allah sent me
to remind you. Hm?

03:09.934 --> 03:12.166
- Sit down.

03:13.100 --> 03:14.800
Help--help me!

03:14.867 --> 03:16.600
- You must go ahead and die.

03:16.667 --> 03:19.934
[straining, groaning]

03:20.000 --> 03:22.667
Ahh! Ahh!

03:24.800 --> 03:26.767
Male announcer: Black Muslim
leader Kareem Said

03:26.834 --> 03:27.800
remains in critical condition

03:27.867 --> 03:29.433
at Oswald State Penitentiary

03:29.500 --> 03:31.367
after a heart attack
last Thursday.

03:31.433 --> 03:33.834
Said--who is serving
five to 18 years

03:33.900 --> 03:35.834
for burning a
white-owned warehouse--

03:35.900 --> 03:38.400
is an outspoken critic of the
American judicial system.

03:38.467 --> 03:41.600
- Oh, man, it's almost
as if he knew.

03:41.667 --> 03:44.867
Man, like, right before
the heart attack,

03:44.934 --> 03:49.066
Said said to me,
he said, "Huseni,

03:49.133 --> 03:51.500
"if anything should happen,

03:51.567 --> 03:54.333
"I want you to gather up
the true believers

03:54.400 --> 03:57.233
"and carry out my work,
carry out my mission.

03:57.300 --> 03:59.033
"Start a holy war
right here in Oz.

03:59.100 --> 04:02.567
A war that will
set fire on the sky."

04:03.500 --> 04:07.100
He said, "Tell them,
my brother, and guide them."

04:08.233 --> 04:10.467
[exhales] Man.

04:14.600 --> 04:17.100
- Hey, hey, look
who's alive.

04:17.166 --> 04:19.800
You know, Said,
I gotta tell you,

04:19.867 --> 04:23.100
odds were 60-40
you were worm's meat.

04:23.166 --> 04:24.567
Yo, Groves,
go get Dr. Nathan

04:24.633 --> 04:26.200
and tell her Said
finally woke up.

04:26.266 --> 04:27.934
Yo, you're gonna
pull something out, man.

04:28.000 --> 04:29.367
- Said, you shouldn't
be doing that.

04:29.433 --> 04:31.467
- Stupid nigger.

04:33.233 --> 04:36.967
- Groves--groves,
get a doctor!

04:38.266 --> 04:43.266
- You...

04:43.333 --> 04:45.200
get my clothes.

04:45.266 --> 04:47.300
Now.

04:49.667 --> 04:51.500
- Again.

04:51.567 --> 04:54.700
- I'm telling you,
I'm perfectly well.

04:54.767 --> 04:57.200
- You had a heart attack.
You nearly died.

04:57.266 --> 05:00.166
- But I didn't, did I?
Excuse me.

05:00.233 --> 05:01.233
- Yeah, this time
you were lucky.

05:01.300 --> 05:02.734
What if it
happens again?

05:02.800 --> 05:04.166
- Well, believe me, Doctor,

05:04.233 --> 05:06.500
I now know what I must do
to keep alive.

05:06.567 --> 05:09.300
McManus, I'm ready
to go back to Em City.

05:09.367 --> 05:11.133
- Okay, but you have to
start taking the medicine

05:11.200 --> 05:13.200
Dr. Nathan prescribed.

05:13.266 --> 05:16.333
Agreed?

05:16.400 --> 05:18.834
- Agreed.

05:18.900 --> 05:21.033
I know. This way.

05:28.233 --> 05:31.567
- People do terrible things
to people.

05:31.633 --> 05:34.233
That's why we got so many
prisons in the world.

05:34.300 --> 05:36.667
People rape other people,

05:36.734 --> 05:40.100
they rob and beat
and cheat other people.

05:40.166 --> 05:44.367
But the worst crime of all
is betrayal.

05:44.433 --> 05:46.767
And there ain't no
jail terms for that.

05:52.033 --> 05:55.667
- Huseni Mershah!

05:57.266 --> 06:00.600
- Praise Allah, praise Allah.

06:00.667 --> 06:05.834
- You saw that I was dying,
and yet, you walked away?

06:05.900 --> 06:07.033
You wanted me to die.

06:07.100 --> 06:08.533
- No Kareem, come on, bro.

06:08.600 --> 06:10.767
I would never want you--
- No!

06:10.834 --> 06:13.066
This man is not our brother
he is our enemy.

06:13.133 --> 06:15.200
As of this moment,
this man is cast out!

06:15.266 --> 06:16.900
No Muslim will speak to him,

06:16.967 --> 06:18.934
look him in the eye
or acknowledge him.

06:19.000 --> 06:21.867
You wanted the
death of another?

06:21.934 --> 06:24.467
Right now you're
dead to us all.

06:27.834 --> 06:30.233
- Kidnapped the president's wife
without a plan.

06:30.300 --> 06:32.600
Kidnapped the president's
wife without a plan.

06:32.667 --> 06:34.200
Yeah, I got a plan.

06:34.266 --> 06:36.567
It's etched with a knife
in the center of my hand.

06:36.633 --> 06:38.834
So I guess I'm going to have
to keep my fist clenched,

06:38.900 --> 06:41.633
walk around D.C. in the rain
till my 'wears is drenched,

06:41.700 --> 06:43.734
wait for that motherfucker
to take out the garbage

06:43.800 --> 06:46.633
and do a press conference about
what great shape this country in

06:46.700 --> 06:49.433
and when them welfare cuts
going to begin.

06:49.500 --> 06:52.033
When he pat his dog
and kiss his wife goodbye,

06:52.100 --> 06:53.633
that's when I move in.

06:53.700 --> 06:55.300
I throw that silly ho
in a headlock.

06:55.367 --> 06:57.300
I muffle her grill
so her screams stop.

06:57.367 --> 06:59.033
I whisper to her,
"Your man ain't here

06:59.100 --> 07:01.266
to protect you, baby, he gone!"

07:01.333 --> 07:02.900
I dial up my nigga O-North

07:02.967 --> 07:04.834
tell him meet me with the Caddy
on the white lawn.

07:04.900 --> 07:06.667
I toss her in the backseat,

07:06.734 --> 07:08.367
I cover her head
with a black sheet,

07:08.433 --> 07:11.200
put the steel of a grill piece,
be like, "If you don't shut up,

07:11.266 --> 07:13.200
"I'ma let two shots off
in your dome piece,

07:13.266 --> 07:15.166
watch you have fits!"

07:15.233 --> 07:16.500
If she don't understand,
I'ma give her the quick

07:16.567 --> 07:17.767
lesson in Ebonics.

07:17.834 --> 07:20.533
"I'm gonna
shoot you, baby."

07:20.600 --> 07:21.867
I take her to my hideout

07:21.934 --> 07:24.033
in the low-income houses
down the street.

07:24.100 --> 07:27.266
I replace her Joan and Davids
with purple Reeboks on her feet.

07:27.333 --> 07:30.266
I give her four hungry kids,
no job, no ambition,

07:30.333 --> 07:33.200
no family support and
a last welfare check.

07:33.266 --> 07:36.400
I give her crappy-ass Medicaid
and an ill type of growth

07:36.467 --> 07:38.367
growing out the side
of her neck.

07:38.433 --> 07:40.166
I tell her,
"Fend for yourself.

07:40.233 --> 07:42.433
Keep you and them shorties
in proper health."

07:42.500 --> 07:44.300
Then, after sufficient time
on that hype,

07:44.367 --> 07:46.033
I'll introduce her
to the-- [inhales sharply]

07:46.100 --> 07:47.400
Crack pipe!

07:47.467 --> 07:49.300
Yeah. I'll let her feel
its soothing effects

07:49.367 --> 07:52.400
as she tries to forget about
the absence of them checks.

07:52.467 --> 07:53.700
I'll make her sell
her jewels for it.

07:53.767 --> 07:56.066
I'll make her
pay her dues for it.

07:56.133 --> 07:59.266
And then I'll come to her
late at night-- [smacking]

07:59.333 --> 08:01.533
And I'll be like,
"Yo, everything ain't

08:01.600 --> 08:03.166
"gonna be all right.

08:03.233 --> 08:05.066
"You ain't going to be able to
go quietly in that good night.

08:05.133 --> 08:08.600
Peace ain't going to come till
your death be done."

08:08.667 --> 08:10.033
And then I'll lead her
up to the roof, ha.

08:10.100 --> 08:13.900
And I'll show her
all the shit she don't own.

08:13.967 --> 08:15.867
I'll lead her
over to the edge.

08:15.934 --> 08:17.834
And leave her there all alone.

08:17.900 --> 08:20.934
[crowd murmuring]

08:23.233 --> 08:26.900
[laughter]
- You can sit at my table, boy.

08:37.600 --> 08:42.633
- Yo. Yo, yo, want to
play that two-on-two? Huh?

08:42.700 --> 08:44.700
Wanna give
that two-on-two?

08:44.767 --> 08:47.533
- Got it, got it, got it.

08:47.600 --> 08:51.467
- Huh? Can I get a ball?
Can I get the ball?

08:51.533 --> 08:54.100
I can't get the ball?

08:54.166 --> 08:56.200
Why don't you
throw me the ball, man?

08:56.266 --> 08:58.633
Arif, you want to
rock some ball, man?

08:58.700 --> 09:01.367
Want to play
some hoop, huh?

09:01.433 --> 09:04.900
Huh, no?
Hoop, man.

09:08.166 --> 09:10.934
- In the name of Allah,
most gracious--

09:11.000 --> 09:14.100
Oh, man, why you gonna do me
like this now? Come on.

09:14.166 --> 09:15.767
- He is Allah,
the one and only.

09:15.834 --> 09:17.867
- Come on, you know I would
never say that

09:17.934 --> 09:20.934
I wanted Said dead.
- Allah the eternal, absolute.

09:21.000 --> 09:23.100
He begets not...
- He's crazy, you know.

09:23.166 --> 09:24.533
- ...Nor is he begotten.

09:24.600 --> 09:25.867
- No, the medication
gone to his head.

09:25.934 --> 09:29.033
- And there are
none like unto him.

09:31.233 --> 09:35.000
In the name of Allah,
most gracious and most merciful.

09:39.867 --> 09:44.033
- Yo, Said, Said.

09:44.100 --> 09:46.934
Don't fall asleep brother,
you might not wake up.

09:58.467 --> 10:02.834
- [muttering]
- Adebisi, Adebisi.

10:02.900 --> 10:05.767
Adebisi, yo, my
African brother.

10:05.834 --> 10:07.834
How you doing?
I gotta talk to you.

10:07.900 --> 10:09.300
- You and me?
- Yeah.

10:09.367 --> 10:10.367
- Talk about what?

10:10.433 --> 10:12.533
- Uh, it's about Said.

10:12.600 --> 10:13.800
Man, you know he's
responsible

10:13.867 --> 10:16.867
for the death of
Jefferson Keane.

10:16.934 --> 10:19.767
- Jefferson Keane?
Ancient history, baby.

10:19.834 --> 10:23.834
- Look, Said,
he got to die.

10:29.834 --> 10:32.867
- [sighs]

10:32.934 --> 10:34.934
I know what's
going on, holy boy.

10:35.000 --> 10:37.967
And I know they
turned their backs on you.

10:38.033 --> 10:41.467
Now, you think
because we have

10:41.533 --> 10:43.367
the same color skin--yeah--

10:43.433 --> 10:45.934
there's some connection?

10:57.100 --> 10:59.533
Go, go, little man. Go.
[grunting]

10:59.600 --> 11:02.467
Try the man next door.

11:02.533 --> 11:06.667
- I'm telling you, Said wanna
start a riot up in here.

11:06.734 --> 11:08.867
He wanna take over Oz.

11:08.934 --> 11:11.133
- Do you have
any evidence?

11:11.200 --> 11:13.333
- No, just what
he told me.

11:13.400 --> 11:15.433
- We need something
more tangible.

11:15.500 --> 11:18.300
Has there been any
stockpiling of weapons?

11:18.367 --> 11:20.967
- Just the usual jobs, homemade.

11:21.033 --> 11:23.800
- Mershah, why are
you doing this?

11:23.867 --> 11:25.433
Why are you giving up Said?

11:25.500 --> 11:26.967
- I wanna stop the violence.

11:27.033 --> 11:28.734
- That is bullshit.
- McManus!

11:28.800 --> 11:31.767
- Leo, you know as well
as I do why he's here!

11:31.834 --> 11:35.133
You're so fucking transparent,
it's laughable!

11:35.200 --> 11:36.367
Officer,

11:36.433 --> 11:37.834
get him the fuck
out of here.

11:37.900 --> 11:39.400
- Oh, look, look, look,
no wait.

11:39.467 --> 11:41.066
I'm telling you, man.
- Out!

11:41.133 --> 11:43.166
[talking over each other]
Get out!

11:44.767 --> 11:48.000
- His motive for betraying Said
isn't important.

11:48.066 --> 11:49.333
His information is.

11:49.400 --> 11:52.867
- Leo, we're not gonna
get anything out of him.

11:52.934 --> 11:54.266
He's clearly
out of the loop.

11:54.333 --> 11:55.633
I want to move him
to another cellblock.

11:55.700 --> 11:57.300
- Why?
- Because I don't want

11:57.367 --> 11:59.400
the bad blood that's happening
between him and Said

11:59.467 --> 12:01.767
to erupt into
something bigger.

12:01.834 --> 12:03.834
He's out!

12:03.900 --> 12:05.767
- All right.

12:05.834 --> 12:08.000
When was the last shakedown
you had in Em City?

12:08.066 --> 12:09.300
- A couple of weeks ago.

12:09.367 --> 12:11.934
- Well, I think it's
time for another.

12:13.967 --> 12:16.400
- Shakedown.
[alarm buzzing]

12:16.467 --> 12:19.500
[indistinct]

12:21.633 --> 12:24.233
[indistinct chatter]

12:24.300 --> 12:27.734
- Fuck you, skid.
Man, get off me.

12:27.800 --> 12:29.533
- What do you got
in your pockets?

12:29.600 --> 12:32.133
- Shut the fuck up.
- Put it in the bag.

12:32.200 --> 12:34.300
- Look what I have.

12:43.834 --> 12:45.867
- Ah! Ah!

12:54.934 --> 12:57.800
- Gentlemen, I can't
put you all in the Hole

12:57.867 --> 13:00.967
because the Hole
is full right now.

13:01.033 --> 13:02.934
And I can't transfer
you out of Emerald City

13:03.000 --> 13:05.934
because all the cells in Oz
happen to be full, too.

13:06.000 --> 13:08.133
But what I can do is
take away your privileges.

13:08.200 --> 13:13.934
No TV, no gym, no phone calls
for one month.

13:14.000 --> 13:16.767
- Gee, Dad, I hope I can
still make it to the prom.

13:16.834 --> 13:19.033
[laughter]
- Two months!

13:19.100 --> 13:21.467
You happy, Alvarez?
That's all.

13:22.433 --> 13:25.467
[indistinct chatter]

13:28.066 --> 13:29.467
You know,

13:29.533 --> 13:32.400
looks like everybody
but Said has a weapon.

13:32.467 --> 13:35.266
- Oh, he ain't stupid.

13:40.500 --> 13:41.934
- Yo, who was the rat?

13:42.000 --> 13:45.767
- I hear it's Mershah.

13:45.834 --> 13:48.867
[man singing Muslim prayer]

14:23.467 --> 14:25.200
- You know something?

14:25.266 --> 14:28.266
Kareem, you're supposed
to be an Iman,

14:28.333 --> 14:30.867
a teacher,

14:30.934 --> 14:33.600
and all you taught me
was that your God

14:33.667 --> 14:36.100
is full of
hate and vengeance.

14:37.233 --> 14:40.934
So you better
watch out, okay?

14:41.000 --> 14:44.300
'Cause he could turn on you,
just like he turned on me.

15:01.233 --> 15:02.800
[indistinct chatter]

15:02.867 --> 15:04.166
- You wanna kill a man?

15:04.233 --> 15:06.900
Stick a shank in his chest.
[spitting]

15:20.367 --> 15:21.967
You wanna torture a man,

15:22.033 --> 15:24.166
feed his loneliness.

15:24.233 --> 15:26.433
Fiending for friendship,
for peace,

15:26.500 --> 15:29.200
he will search everywhere.

15:33.333 --> 15:36.200
And when he realizes
that he won't find it,

15:36.266 --> 15:38.967
he will destroy himself.

15:42.800 --> 15:46.100
- I have asked you here
because I'm a worried man.

15:46.166 --> 15:49.100
The death of Huseni Mershah
is yet another example of

15:49.166 --> 15:51.166
of the brutality that
we suffer here.

15:51.233 --> 15:52.834
- But his death
was a suicide.

15:52.900 --> 15:54.834
- That is what the
authorities have claimed,

15:54.900 --> 15:57.767
but what I know is,
six men have died

15:57.834 --> 16:00.066
under bizarre circumstances.

16:00.133 --> 16:04.567
Suffocation, fire, mutilation.

16:04.633 --> 16:06.800
And the list continues on.

16:06.867 --> 16:10.166
And Warden Glynn sits
in his office, aloof.

16:10.233 --> 16:13.367
Now, the FBI was brought in
to do an investigation,

16:13.433 --> 16:14.934
but where is
their report?

16:15.000 --> 16:18.633
- Are you saying it's
been repressed?

16:18.700 --> 16:20.467
- I don't know.

16:20.533 --> 16:25.266
I asked the question in the hope
that you, the press,

16:25.333 --> 16:27.200
can find out.

16:27.266 --> 16:29.033
'cause we prisoners
of Oz, I believe,

16:29.100 --> 16:32.767
will sit here waiting for
answers that never come.

16:33.333 --> 16:35.133
- The FBI investigation
into the deaths

16:35.200 --> 16:37.567
at Oswald State Penitentiary
is ongoing.

16:37.633 --> 16:39.467
We're not about to rush it
just to satisfy

16:39.533 --> 16:41.133
the media or the inmates.

16:41.200 --> 16:44.934
We intend to do our work
thoroughly and completely.

16:45.000 --> 16:47.934
- Your little television show
got everybody's attention.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.266
But I'm afraid that was
your last performance.

16:50.333 --> 16:51.500
I'm ordering
a press blackout.

16:51.567 --> 16:55.767
- Warden, can't you see?

16:55.834 --> 16:59.567
Now, why is blackout
a big, bad thing?

16:59.633 --> 17:02.400
You can get White-Out
in a little bottle.

17:02.467 --> 17:05.200
- Don't be smug.
Don't you be smug with me,

17:05.266 --> 17:07.400
you son-of-a-bitch.

17:07.467 --> 17:09.800
From the first day
you got here,

17:09.867 --> 17:13.266
you have tried to destroy
everything that I built

17:13.333 --> 17:14.700
and everything
that I stand for.

17:14.767 --> 17:18.066
- Oh, that is pride!

17:18.133 --> 17:21.300
[sighs]
I know that well.

17:21.367 --> 17:24.500
McManus, you've given yourself
far too much importance.

17:24.567 --> 17:27.333
You see, because this thing
is larger than you.

17:27.400 --> 17:29.467
It's larger than me.

17:29.533 --> 17:31.834
So go ahead,
take the media away.

17:31.900 --> 17:33.166
Give us a blackout.

17:33.233 --> 17:36.233
Censor our letters,
tape our mouths shut.

17:38.967 --> 17:41.667
There will always be
a man to tell the truth.

17:46.500 --> 17:49.000
The truth will be heard.

17:53.667 --> 17:55.800
May I go now?

17:55.867 --> 17:58.000
'Cause it is time
for me to pray.

18:01.300 --> 18:04.433
[singing Muslim prayer]

18:04.500 --> 18:06.066
[bell rings]
- Listen up.

18:06.133 --> 18:08.200
Here are some new rules
from the Warden.

18:08.266 --> 18:12.166
"As of today, no inmate will be
allowed to use prayer beads,

18:12.233 --> 18:16.333
"prayer mats or special oils for
religious or other purposes.

18:16.400 --> 18:19.000
"Inmates will no longer be
allowed to wear

18:19.066 --> 18:21.066
"similar clothing
or head apparel

18:21.133 --> 18:25.533
identifying them as a member
of any group, gang or cult."

18:27.367 --> 18:28.533
- Whoa, whoa!

18:28.600 --> 18:32.000
No, no!

18:34.367 --> 18:36.200
Now, you do realize this is
a violation of our right

18:36.266 --> 18:38.200
to freely practice
our religion.

18:38.266 --> 18:40.033
- You can practice
all you want.

18:40.100 --> 18:42.066
Pray till the
cows come home.

18:42.133 --> 18:44.333
The Constitution does not
guarantee that you,

18:44.400 --> 18:47.500
as a prisoner
have the right to any stuff.

18:48.233 --> 18:49.667
- Easy!

18:49.734 --> 18:51.900
- You're going to
have to hand it over.

18:54.700 --> 18:57.433
Look, this can go
one of two ways.

18:57.500 --> 18:59.633
I vote for no blood.

19:04.967 --> 19:08.700
- This is a meaningless
gesture, brothers.

19:08.767 --> 19:11.934
Our faith is not in kufis,
beads or mats.

19:13.767 --> 19:15.834
It is in our hearts.

19:25.834 --> 19:28.133
- All right, let's go.
- All right, everyone,

19:28.200 --> 19:30.600
can I have your attention,
please?

19:30.667 --> 19:32.734
I've got some news
for you all.

19:32.800 --> 19:36.367
The FBI report will
be released today,

19:36.433 --> 19:38.100
and it will
state emphatically

19:38.166 --> 19:41.367
that Sanchez, Ortolani,

19:41.433 --> 19:44.700
Post, Martinez
and Markstrom

19:44.767 --> 19:46.867
were all killed
by inmates.

19:46.934 --> 19:49.633
[booing and yelling]

19:49.700 --> 19:51.734
Quiet down!

19:53.100 --> 19:57.133
The death of Huseni Mershah
has been ruled a suicide.

19:57.200 --> 19:58.667
[all banging]

19:58.734 --> 20:02.200
Stop it!

20:02.266 --> 20:05.233
Though it is likely that
some correctional officers

20:05.300 --> 20:07.767
may have been involved...

20:07.834 --> 20:11.000
in a secondary manner
with some of the murders.

20:11.834 --> 20:13.900
Knock it off!

20:16.834 --> 20:17.800
People, if you
don't knock it off,

20:17.867 --> 20:19.433
I'm not gonna be able to finish.

20:19.500 --> 20:22.533
[banging continues]

20:24.934 --> 20:27.266
Fine.

20:37.200 --> 20:40.233
[cheering]

20:51.633 --> 20:53.066
- When you stand up,
look in the mirror

20:53.133 --> 20:56.467
and say, like Solomon,
"I am black, but I am humbly--

20:56.533 --> 20:59.066
- [sharp whistling]
- Come on, let's go.

20:59.133 --> 21:02.734
- Go, go, go.

21:02.800 --> 21:04.567
- Mr. Said...

21:04.633 --> 21:06.667
- Hmm?

21:06.734 --> 21:09.367
- I just wanted to
tell you that

21:09.433 --> 21:11.767
the whole thing
with the spoons,

21:11.834 --> 21:14.734
the whole Allah thing,
it's awesome.

21:16.900 --> 21:19.400
The salami, I like him.

21:31.100 --> 21:32.867
- So what's up?

21:32.934 --> 21:35.166
You turning Muslim on me?

21:35.233 --> 21:37.700
- Hm?

21:37.767 --> 21:39.633
He's a great speaker,
that Said.

21:39.700 --> 21:41.934
He says our lives are crap
because of Glynn and McManus

21:42.033 --> 21:44.467
and the rest.

21:44.533 --> 21:48.133
Said says that Glynn's
guilty of worse crimes

21:48.200 --> 21:50.233
than any of us
have committed.

21:52.734 --> 21:53.734
You ever kill anybody?

21:53.800 --> 21:56.967
- Mm-mm. No, I ain't
done nothing.

21:58.266 --> 22:01.467
[sighs] I got a bum rap,
you know?

22:01.533 --> 22:04.133
I'm inn-o-cent.

22:04.200 --> 22:06.467
- I thought it'd be hard
to murder my parents,

22:06.533 --> 22:10.900
but it wasn't.
- Hey, how'd you whack 'em?

22:12.567 --> 22:15.734
- Ah, Ball-peen hammer.

22:20.867 --> 22:24.367
- Prisoner #97G414,
Donald Groves.

22:24.433 --> 22:27.200
Convicted July 3rd, '97,
two counts,

22:27.266 --> 22:28.533
murder in
the first-degree.

22:28.600 --> 22:30.867
Sentence: life imprisonment.

22:32.633 --> 22:36.000
I think I should
kill Warden Glynn.

22:36.066 --> 22:37.467
- What?

22:37.533 --> 22:40.667
- I think I ought to
kill Glynn.

22:41.000 --> 22:43.500
- [chuckles]
All right, look, this is what

22:43.567 --> 22:45.700
you should do, all right?

22:45.767 --> 22:47.767
You know that chick,
Dr. Nathan, all right?

22:47.834 --> 22:51.266
You go to her and you tell her
to write you a prescription.

22:51.333 --> 22:53.667
I'm telling you, she's got me
on these anti-depressants

22:53.734 --> 22:57.467
right now and I'm like--

22:57.533 --> 22:59.400
I'm sailing, man.

22:59.467 --> 23:02.233
- No.

23:02.300 --> 23:04.967
My first idea is best.

23:05.033 --> 23:07.200
Next chance I get,
I'll murder Glynn.

23:08.867 --> 23:11.033
- Look out!
- Oh!

23:11.100 --> 23:13.600
- Ohh! Oh!

23:15.734 --> 23:17.834
[gavel banging]

23:17.900 --> 23:21.700
- Donald Groves,
convicted August 21st, '97,

23:21.767 --> 23:23.600
murder in the first degree
in the death

23:23.667 --> 23:26.166
of corrections officer
Lawrence Smith.

23:26.233 --> 23:30.100
Sentence: death.

23:30.166 --> 23:33.166
This is a genocide.

23:33.233 --> 23:36.100
Killing murderers
is genocide.

23:40.033 --> 23:43.367
- Groves?

23:43.433 --> 23:45.200
- They beat me.
- Who?

23:49.867 --> 23:53.900
Groves, you have been
condemned to die

23:53.967 --> 23:55.900
for the murder
of Officer Smith.

23:55.967 --> 23:57.834
The State gives you
the right to choose

23:57.900 --> 24:00.800
any method you wish to die.

24:00.867 --> 24:03.133
- I shouldn't even be
talking to you.

24:03.200 --> 24:05.433
You should be dead.

24:05.500 --> 24:07.667
You were the one
that was supposed to die.

24:07.734 --> 24:09.767
- How do you
want to die, Groves?

24:09.834 --> 24:11.600
Lethal injection,
electric chair?

24:11.667 --> 24:12.600
- Firing squad.

24:12.667 --> 24:14.300
- Firing squad?

24:14.367 --> 24:16.400
- Isn't that what they
do to assassins?

24:16.467 --> 24:18.066
- Fine.

24:18.133 --> 24:22.200
I'm going to personally  paint
the target on your heart.

24:22.266 --> 24:23.300
- Warden,

24:23.367 --> 24:24.500
Warden...

24:26.467 --> 24:29.700
Me killing you
wasn't personal, you know?

24:30.900 --> 24:32.934
It just had to be done.

24:38.033 --> 24:40.633
- When your shift's over,
come to my office.

24:40.700 --> 24:43.600
I want you to tell me why
I shouldn't fire  your asses.

24:45.233 --> 24:49.433
- Lawrence Smith
was an outstanding officer.

24:49.500 --> 24:52.633
He was an outstanding
human being.

24:52.700 --> 24:55.967
And he died for what
he truly believed in:

24:56.033 --> 24:57.066
justice.

24:58.900 --> 25:01.200
I think it would be
easier to get angry,

25:01.266 --> 25:03.734
to punish all the inmates

25:03.800 --> 25:05.700
for a crime committed
by one of them.

25:07.367 --> 25:10.233
- [groans]
Uhh...

25:10.300 --> 25:11.867
Ahh...

25:11.934 --> 25:13.900
- But knowing Lawrence,

25:13.967 --> 25:15.600
I don't think that
he would want his death

25:15.667 --> 25:18.800
to bring about more pain,
more suffering.

25:18.867 --> 25:20.934
[overlapping yelling]

25:27.500 --> 25:30.967
I think that he would want
his death to bring about...

25:31.033 --> 25:32.333
peace.

25:37.967 --> 25:39.500
[guard laughing]

25:45.934 --> 25:47.400
- You want to
get a drink?

25:47.467 --> 25:49.533
- No, no, I got
a press conference.

25:49.600 --> 25:50.967
- Oh, that sounds
like fun.

25:51.033 --> 25:53.500
- Warden?
- Yes, Eddie?

25:53.567 --> 25:56.000
- Did I hear right--
Groves wants a firing squad?

25:56.066 --> 25:57.667
- Yeah, the sick bastard.

25:57.734 --> 25:59.500
- Do we have
a firing squad?

25:59.567 --> 26:01.667
- No, I got to
put one together.

26:01.734 --> 26:04.333
- I'd like to volunteer.

26:04.400 --> 26:06.100
- Why?

26:06.166 --> 26:08.633
- Smitty was my friend.

26:08.700 --> 26:10.767
- You know, in this case,
I'm not sure

26:10.834 --> 26:12.500
if that's a good
enough reason, Eddie, I mean...

26:12.567 --> 26:15.967
this isn't about revenge,
it's about the law.

26:16.033 --> 26:17.700
But, uh...

26:18.967 --> 26:21.066
I'll get back to you.

26:23.800 --> 26:25.467
Gloria,
you wanted to see me?

26:25.533 --> 26:27.066
- Yeah. You're done.

26:27.133 --> 26:28.567
Look around--we got
a bumper crop

26:28.633 --> 26:30.533
of officer-related
injuries.

26:30.600 --> 26:33.133
- O'Reily,
what happened?

26:33.200 --> 26:35.667
- He hit me.
I wasn't doing dick,

26:35.734 --> 26:37.233
I swear,
and he just ups and hits me.

26:37.300 --> 26:39.266
- Who?
- Yeah, right.

26:39.333 --> 26:42.834
I tell you, and next time
I get it worse.

26:42.900 --> 26:45.233
- Take that.
Leo, look,

26:45.300 --> 26:47.433
since Smith's murder,
this ER's SRO!

26:47.500 --> 26:49.367
I'm telling you, your officers
are out of control.

26:49.433 --> 26:52.467
- You've gotta do something.
- I know, I know.

26:52.533 --> 26:53.967
I know.

26:54.300 --> 26:56.633
- "You know."
[whispers] Jesus...

26:56.700 --> 26:59.133
- Are you saying that
random reprisals are justified?

26:59.200 --> 27:00.667
- Yeah.

27:00.734 --> 27:03.400
- Well, one person killed
Lawrence Smith...

27:03.467 --> 27:05.367
Groves. The other inmates
are innocent.

27:05.433 --> 27:07.166
- Innocent?
Christ!

27:07.233 --> 27:09.266
I didn't expect you to
understand, McManus.

27:09.333 --> 27:11.800
- What do you mean?
- You were never a guard.

27:11.867 --> 27:13.467
Huh? You didn't come up
through the ranks,

27:13.533 --> 27:15.433
like Leo, me,
the rest of them.

27:15.500 --> 27:18.033
- So I don't understand
the anger, the frustration

27:18.100 --> 27:19.600
that COs go through?

27:19.667 --> 27:21.066
That's fucking bullshit.

27:21.133 --> 27:23.066
- Look, Leo, you cannot keep
suspending these guys

27:23.133 --> 27:24.767
just because they slap
some dipshit around.

27:24.834 --> 27:26.567
- Well, I can't condone it,
either, Lenny.

27:26.633 --> 27:28.200
- We're understaffed as it is.

27:28.266 --> 27:30.000
You took experienced officers
off of the rotation.

27:30.066 --> 27:31.300
What're you
leaving us with?

27:31.367 --> 27:33.333
Newbies who can't
handle a crisis.

27:33.400 --> 27:35.000
- So what do you
suggest I do?

27:35.066 --> 27:37.300
- Just let our guys get through
Groves' execution.

27:37.367 --> 27:40.066
Once he's in a body bag,
this whole thing'll fade away.

27:40.133 --> 27:43.500
- So in the meantime, they
whale on whoever they want?

27:43.567 --> 27:45.033
- Reality's hard for you,
isn't it, McManus?

27:45.100 --> 27:48.000
[bell ringing]

27:49.667 --> 27:52.800
[background chatter]

28:03.133 --> 28:04.633
- Hi.

28:04.700 --> 28:07.100
I'm Officer Gordon Wood,
here replacing Vogelsang.

28:07.166 --> 28:08.533
- Well, hi.

28:08.600 --> 28:11.633
Vogelsang's a good man, but he
can't control his temper.

28:11.700 --> 28:13.934
How long you been
working at Oz?

28:14.000 --> 28:15.166
- Three weeks.
- Ha.

28:15.233 --> 28:16.834
A veteran, huh?
- [chuckles] Hmm.

28:16.900 --> 28:19.467
- Okay, if you got
questions, ask.

28:19.533 --> 28:22.667
It doesn't make you stupid.
It may save both our lives.

28:22.734 --> 28:24.200
- I hear you.

28:24.266 --> 28:26.533
Is that Kareem Said?

28:26.600 --> 28:28.200
- Yep, in the flesh.

28:28.266 --> 28:30.066
- Hmm. He don't look
so tough.

28:30.133 --> 28:32.633
- Yeah, well,
looks are deceiving.

28:37.867 --> 28:40.033
- My laundry
interests you?

28:40.100 --> 28:43.000
- Yeah.
I always wondered, uh,

28:43.066 --> 28:45.867
famous guy like
Kareem Said,

28:45.934 --> 28:47.867
is he a Fruit of the Loom
or a Haines man?

28:47.934 --> 28:49.533
- I don't wear underwear.

28:49.600 --> 28:51.500
- Oh. Ha ha.
I see.

28:51.567 --> 28:54.066
You, uh, you like the
wide-open spaces, huh?

28:54.133 --> 28:57.400
- That's right.
- Oh, well...

28:57.467 --> 28:59.433
Asalaam alaikum.

29:07.700 --> 29:10.633
[dramatic chords]

29:13.033 --> 29:16.033
- It is with enormous
sadness and respect

29:16.100 --> 29:18.033
that I present to
Loretta Smith

29:18.100 --> 29:22.667
the Fleishman Medal of Honor
in memory of her son,

29:22.734 --> 29:24.400
Officer Lawrence Smith,

29:24.467 --> 29:27.300
who died in the service
of this great State.

29:27.367 --> 29:28.500
[reporters chattering]
- Mrs. Smith,

29:28.567 --> 29:30.000
do you feel justice
has been served?

29:31.500 --> 29:34.400
- I would like to be able
to watch the execution.

29:35.867 --> 29:38.467
- Mrs. Smith, I don't
think that's a good idea.

29:38.533 --> 29:40.600
- Besides,
the State doesn't allow

29:40.667 --> 29:42.333
family members
to be present.

29:44.367 --> 29:47.400
If I could help,
believe me, I would.

29:49.567 --> 29:51.734
- Can I see Groves?

29:52.867 --> 29:55.467
- I'm not sure what
good that'll do.

29:56.967 --> 30:01.433
- I'm not sure, either,
but you're going to kill him,

30:01.500 --> 30:03.800
and he'll be dead and buried

30:03.867 --> 30:05.734
and I won't get another chance.

30:16.567 --> 30:18.734
I'm Loretta Smith.

30:19.900 --> 30:21.700
You killed my son.

30:25.867 --> 30:29.000
You're a handsome fellow.

30:29.066 --> 30:30.533
- Thanks.

30:31.633 --> 30:34.767
- You broke God's law,
"love thy neighbor".

30:38.800 --> 30:41.600
I want to hate you,
but I can't.

30:42.800 --> 30:46.767
I feel pity and tears,

30:46.834 --> 30:48.333
but no hate.

30:50.500 --> 30:53.567
I didn't realize that
until this moment.

30:57.767 --> 31:01.066
You are my neighbor,
and I love you...

31:02.834 --> 31:05.533
And I forgive you,

31:05.600 --> 31:07.467
with all my heart.

31:12.000 --> 31:13.467
That's all.

31:16.734 --> 31:19.166
- [sobbing softly]

31:19.233 --> 31:21.967
[footsteps retreating]

31:25.266 --> 31:27.467
- First I want to thank you
gentlemen for volunteering

31:27.533 --> 31:29.900
to serve on
the firing squad.

31:29.967 --> 31:33.333
Since we announced to the press
that Groves chose this method,

31:33.400 --> 31:36.734
we've been swamped with
phone calls from sharpshooters

31:36.800 --> 31:39.367
all over the country
wanting to sign up.

31:39.433 --> 31:41.500
But the warden and I
felt it best

31:41.567 --> 31:46.333
if we handled this internally.

31:46.400 --> 31:48.133
Warden?

31:48.200 --> 31:50.266
- There hasn't been an
execution by firing squad

31:50.333 --> 31:52.867
in this state since 1872.

31:52.934 --> 31:55.567
Fortunately, Lenny Burruano
worked in Utah

31:55.633 --> 31:57.767
before coming to Oswald.
Lenny.

31:57.834 --> 31:59.700
- Thank you, Warden.

31:59.767 --> 32:04.000
Many people will tell you that
firing squads are barbaric,

32:04.066 --> 32:05.767
but in fact,

32:05.834 --> 32:10.433
it's a lot more humane
than the electric chair.

32:10.500 --> 32:11.834
In any case,

32:11.900 --> 32:14.100
the protocol for
a successful execution

32:14.166 --> 32:16.900
is proper lighting,
proper distance.

32:16.967 --> 32:19.533
But you must prepare yourself
for the emotional burden

32:19.600 --> 32:21.900
of actually
pulling the trigger.

32:21.967 --> 32:25.166
You should know that one of
the rifles will carry blanks

32:25.233 --> 32:26.600
so that none of you
will ever know

32:26.667 --> 32:28.734
who actually fired
the fatal shots.

32:31.667 --> 32:34.166
[phone rings]

32:34.233 --> 32:35.900
[ringing]

32:35.967 --> 32:37.667
[ringing]

32:38.800 --> 32:40.233
- Hello?

32:40.300 --> 32:41.633
He what?

32:41.700 --> 32:43.533
I'll be right down.

32:45.967 --> 32:47.233
- Patient's name
is Donald Groves.

32:47.300 --> 32:49.100
- Let's put down an NG tube,
pump his stomach!

32:49.166 --> 32:50.900
- What happened?
- Overdose.

32:50.967 --> 32:52.900
- Is he going to live?
- Ask me again in 20 minutes.

32:52.967 --> 32:54.000
- Save him, Doctor.

32:54.066 --> 32:55.367
Did you strip-search him?
- Yes.

32:55.433 --> 32:57.000
- How the fuck
did he get pills in his cell?

32:57.066 --> 32:58.133
- I don't know.
- Find out!

32:58.200 --> 33:00.100
- We're losing him!
Start CPR!

33:00.166 --> 33:01.800
- Save that little prick.
- What's the difference?

33:01.867 --> 33:03.467
He's scheduled
to die tomorrow anyway.

33:03.533 --> 33:05.567
- The law says that he has to be
aware that he's being executed.

33:05.633 --> 33:07.333
He has to know why
he's being executed.

33:07.400 --> 33:10.300
He has  to be alive,
so save him!

33:10.367 --> 33:12.100
Save his God damn ass!

33:20.767 --> 33:23.266
- Rebadow, what are you
doing in here all day?

33:23.333 --> 33:25.166
- Hiding.

33:25.233 --> 33:26.166
- [chuckles]

33:26.233 --> 33:28.100
- Any word on Groves?

33:28.166 --> 33:29.433
- Yeah...

33:29.500 --> 33:31.734
Dr. Nathan brought him
back from the dead.

33:31.800 --> 33:33.367
- A resurrection, huh?

33:33.433 --> 33:37.033
- Yeah. They delayed execution
for a couple of hours.

33:38.800 --> 33:40.233
You miss him, don't you?

33:40.300 --> 33:42.367
- Groves?

33:42.433 --> 33:44.400
No.

33:44.467 --> 33:47.166
I've learned over the years
not to make attachments.

33:47.233 --> 33:50.166
If you do, you spend
all your time grieving.

33:50.233 --> 33:52.066
- You know what?

33:52.133 --> 33:56.700
I think grieving is a helluva
lot better than hiding, man.

34:06.934 --> 34:09.967
- Hail Mary, full of grace,
the Lord is with thee.

34:10.033 --> 34:11.767
Blessed art thou
amongst women

34:11.834 --> 34:12.767
and blessed
is the fruit of--

34:12.834 --> 34:14.633
- Father?
- Yeah?

34:14.700 --> 34:17.767
- I've been thinking a lot
about my final words,

34:17.834 --> 34:20.700
and I've decided
what I wanted to say.

34:20.767 --> 34:24.900
I'd like you to write it down
and give it to Mrs. Smith.

34:24.967 --> 34:28.834
That'll maybe make her
feel better, okay?

34:28.900 --> 34:31.300
Will you do that for me?

34:31.367 --> 34:32.834
- Of course.

34:35.767 --> 34:38.433
I think that she'd
appreciate that.

34:38.500 --> 34:40.233
- It's time.

34:45.166 --> 34:47.500
- It's time.

34:58.834 --> 35:01.166
- The sky's a nice
color of blue.

35:31.033 --> 35:33.467
- Blessed Almighty God,

35:33.533 --> 35:36.400
the Father and the Son
and the Holy Spirit...

35:39.100 --> 35:42.000
Come upon you and
remain with you forever.

35:56.700 --> 35:59.567
[dark chords]

35:59.633 --> 36:01.333
♪ ♪

36:01.400 --> 36:03.133
I just have to
hear his last words.

36:03.200 --> 36:05.200
- You can listen
through this.

36:05.266 --> 36:06.333
- Great.

36:10.500 --> 36:11.967
[slaps paper on]

36:12.033 --> 36:16.600
♪ ♪

36:16.667 --> 36:18.066
- [gasping for breath]

